footnotes.FootnoteText: Test required – passing score not set – verify with state.

Maine All Areas, K–12 (except Career and Technical Education) require (1) meeting the passing score of 150 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Mathematics (5733), meeting the passing score of 156 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Reading (5713), and meeting the passing score of 162 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Writing (5723) or (2) achieving a combined total score of 468 with no single score on any section being more than 3 points lower thant the required score. Career and Technical Education requires (1) meeting the passing score of 147 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Mathematics (5733), meeting the passing score of 153 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Reading (5713), and meeting the passing score of 156 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Writing (5723) or (2) achieving a combined total score of 456 with no single score on any section being more than 3 points lower thant the required score.

North Dakota Licensure for all areas requires meeting a (1) meeting the passing score of 150 on Core Academic Skills for Educators: Mathematics (5733), meeting the passing score of 156 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Reading (5713), and meeting the passing score of 160 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Writing (5723) or (2) acheiving a combined total score of 466  with no score being below the minimum set for each test:  a minimum score of 149 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Reading (5713), a minimum score of 153 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Writing (5723), and a minimum score of 143 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Mathematics (5733).

North Carolina requires (1) meeting the passing score of 150 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Mathematics (5733), meeting the passing score of 156 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Reading (5713), and meeting the passing score of 162 for Core Academic Skills for Educators: Writing (5723) or (2) achieving a combined total score of 468.
This is the preliminary passing score for this test and is subject to change. Please contact the Utah State Board of Education for details.
